article.headline: UCF 72, S. Dakota St. 61
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Jermaine Taylor scored 26 points and Lavell Payne added 13 points and 12 rebounds to lead Central Florida to a 72-61 win over South Dakota State on Saturday. Taylor had 15 points in the second half for the Golden Knights (11-3), who have won three of their last four games. Taylor was 9-for-14 from the field, a total that included six 3-pointers. UCF was 10-for-24 from 3-point range. Josh Peppers' 3-pointer 40 seconds into the game put the Golden Knights on top. Garrett Callahan had two free throws to give SDSU a 4-3 lead with 17:40 to play, but UCF went back on top the next time down the floor and stayed there. The Golden Knights shot 46 percent in the first half to take a 34-28 halftime lead. They started the second half on a 14-6 run and went up 59-44 for their largest lead midway through the second half. The Jackrabbits (4-13) got within with six on a Matt Cadwell 3-pointer with 2:41 to play and within six again at 1:49. But they never got closer. Callahan led the Jackrabbits with 21 points and seven rebounds. Cadwell scored 14 points and Kai Williams 13. Mike O'Donnell had 14 points for UCF.
